	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The boot ROM is a Flash chip inside the PowerPak, to modify it you have to reprogram that chip. However, it appears that the menu itself is not in the boot ROM (which contains routines for interfacing with the CF card and other "behind the curtains" stuff), but in one of the files that goes in the CF card, so it might actually be possible to change it. I don't know which file it is, though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


